        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:41PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and thunderstorms
with gusty winds over Madison County. Movement was north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Three Forks, Manhattan, Whitehall, Pony, Silver Star, Harrison,
Norris, Mcallister, Waterloo, Missouri Headwaters State Park,
Cardwell, Logan, Lewis And Clark Caverns State Park, Amsterdam,
Trident, Willow Creek, and Madison Buffalo Jump State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
